ğŸš¨ pthread_mutex
Used inside each thread to control access to shared resources:
Forks â†’ pthread_mutex_lock(left_fork) ensures only one philosopher can take a fork.
Printing â†’ pthread_mutex_lock(print_lock) ensures that only one message prints at a time.
Death checking â†’ pthread_mutex_lock(death_lock) prevents race conditions in checking philosopher deaths.

Concept	Behavior
Threads Run Simultaneously?	âœ… Yes, each thread runs independently after pthread_create().
Does pthread_join() make them sequential?	âŒ No, it only makes main() wait for them to finish.
Is pthread_join() necessary?	âœ… Yes, to avoid main() exiting early and killing all threads.
